PrecisINDIAN INCOME TAX REMISSION ORDER - which provides for the remission of 1992 and 1993 income tax payable by Indians whose wages were paid by an employer whose office was situated on a reserve or in an Indian settlement as well as for the remission of income tax payable on certain Unemployment Insurance benefits received by Indians between 1985 and 1991, in accordance with the 1992 ruling of the Supreme Court of Canada (William v. R.).
